AI-> learing, reasoning, problem solving, understand natural language, even perceptions. it is done by using ML
ML- subset of AI that focuses on building machines that can learn from & make decisions based on data
teaching computers to learn from experience instead of programming explicit instructions we provide system with data &
algorithem that allow it to learn and improve over time.
ex: identify images

ML can do complex tasks like supervised(Input data with lables) and Unsupervised(input data without labels) and 
Reinforcement (learn from feedback/experience)

Token: AI models breaks text in units called Tokens. subword level token, character level tokenization
Embeddings: are numerical representations of real-world objects that ML and AI systems use to understand complex 
knowledge domains like humans do

A word token is converted into embeddings, which are vector representation of words, and then it is fed to the 
neural networks for further processing. neural networks need these embeddings for any kind of processing.
Input Text -> Tokenization -> Embedding Generation -> Model processing

Prompt Engineering:  
ChatGPT: write a deployment yaml file for kubernetes (Text Generation)
Dall-E: create an image of a Web App Architecture Diagram (Image Generation)
Copilot: Write code to Dockerize an application (Code Generation)

strategies in prompt engineering:
* zero shot: write terraform script to create an EC2 in AWS
* one-shot: give this example to chatgpt or AI systems where a python script checks for null password entries 
(if password is not none), identify security flaws in the following python login script
* few-shot: provide some examples of terraform scripts with marked security improvements. now analyze this new terraform
script and suggest security enhancements
* chain of thought: explain step by step how you would debug a failing kubernetes pod based on these error logs and 
system status.

